Examples the text gives of types of matter that are easy to identify with sight and touch senses
rocks , trees , bicycles , and different kinds of animals
Types of matter more challenging to observe
two separate properties : physical and chemical
several different physical properties that are outlined in the article
density , ductility , malleability , boiling point , melting point , electrical conductivity , and solubility
The author references clay as an object that is malleable as it has the ability to take different forms by pressing or pounding on it .
an object that is malleable as it has the ability to take different forms by pressing or pounding on it
that physical change only relates to the size and shape of the object
The difference between physical and chemical change

paper folded into thirds , although the new paper size is now one third of the original
the original type of matter : paper

a rule associated with forms of energy
